  19 Sep 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  change order of GIT repos

  16 Sep 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] use system expat instead of bundled version

  28 Aug 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] sync with portage

  28 Aug 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> -simgear-2.8.0.ebuild:
  Remove simgear-2.8 and flightgear-2.8. Both in tree now

  26 Aug 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] remove freealut dep, depend on openal

*simgear-2.8.0 (17 Aug 2012)

  17 Aug 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> -simgear-2.6.0.ebuild,
  +simgear-2.8.0.ebuild:
  [games-simulation/flightgear] version bump to 2.8.0.
  Uses dynamic linking now

  07 Jul 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  games-simulation/flightgear,games-utils/terragear-cs] compile with dynamic
  linking.
  Only for the live versions for now.

  12 Jun 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  [games-simulation/flightgear-9999 and deps] add a second git server
  as fallback and set the name of the local clone to make sure the same
  directory is used for both server checkouts

  07 Jun 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-2.6.0.ebuild:
  2.6.0, games-simulation/flightgear-2.6.0] mark ~x86, according to feedback,
  move FG to EAPI 4

  31 May 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] switch back to official GIT url

*simgear-2.6.0 (24 Apr 2012)

  24 Apr 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> +simgear-2.6.0.ebuild:
  [games-simulation/flightgear, dev-games/simgear]: new ebuilds for version
  2.6.0

  Based on the live ebuilds (thus tested already). Hope this gets into
  portage soon.

  24 Apr 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> metadata.xml,
  simgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] EAPI4, reduce deps when compiling the headless version.
  Change git URL to mirror. Document useflags

  11 Nov 2011; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> simgear-9999.ebuild:
  games-simulation/flightgear]: support headless mode
  in simgear, some fixes to flightgear

  02 Nov 2011; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> -simgear-2.4.0.ebuild:
  games-simulation/flightgear] remove 2.4.0 versions (in tree)

